{"id":735,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":735,"title":"Judas","subtitle":"","short_title":"Judas","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.t1","order":".000.1912"},[".title","Judas"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p1","order":".000.1913"},"(1) Maccabaeus (see",["i",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/maccabees"},"Maccabees"]],")."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p2","order":".000.1914"},"(2) Iscariot, meaning “belonging to Kerioth” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/15.25"},"Josh. 15:25"],") in the tribe of Judah, one of “the twelve,” and the only one who was not a Galilean. The passages in which he is mentioned are",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/10.4"},"Matt. 10:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/26.14"},"26:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3.19"},"Mark 3:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/14.10"},"14:10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/6.16"},"Luke 6:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/22.3"},"22:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/6.71"},"John 6:71"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/12.4"},"12:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/13.2,26"},"13:2, 26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/1.16,25"},"Acts 1:16, 25"],"."],["div",{"id":"p3","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p3","order":".000.1915"},"(3) A brother of our Lord (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/13.55"},"Matt. 13:55"],"); writer of the epistle of Jude (see also",["i",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/brethren-of-the-lord"},"Brethren of the Lord"]],")."],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p4","order":".000.1916"},"(4) “Not Iscariot,” one of the Twelve, also called Judas (son or brother) of James (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/6.16"},"Luke 6:16"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/14.22"},"John 14:22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/1.13"},"Acts 1:13"],"); probably the same as Lebbaeus or Thaddaeus (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/10.3"},"Matt. 10:3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/3.18"},"Mark 3:18"],")."],["div",{"id":"p5","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p5","order":".000.1917"},"(5) Of Galilee, leader of a revolt against Roman rule “in the days of the taxing” (of the census); regarded by many as the Messiah. He had a great following but was defeated and slain (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/5.37"},"Acts 5:37"],")."],["div",{"id":"p6","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p6","order":".000.1918"},"(6) Surnamed Barsabbas, a leading member of the Church in Jerusalem (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/15.22,27,32"},"Acts 15:22, 27, 32"],")."],["div",{"id":"p7","uri":"/scriptures/bd/judas.p7","order":".000.1919"},"(7) A man of Damascus with whom Paul lodged after his conversion (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/9.11"},"Acts 9:11"],")."]]],"refs":null}
